data.status: Match tied (Islamabad United won the one-over eliminator)

comm_lines.comm: Oh these low-scorers .. they're playing around with my blood pressure. Live the madness, scroll through it while we get set to set off. To imagine a day that started with rain ends up well past midnight with drama that Pakistan is forever waiting to produce. I've been Vineet Anantharaman bringing you all the action in the company of Akshay Maanay and our scorer Vinod. Ta ta!!

Misbah, winning skipper: We needed a match like this. We haven't been playing good cricket but this match will give us a lot of confidence. Specially happy to see the way we fielded, that's what brought the game back for us. I think in T20 cricket you know that without fielding well you won't be part of many teams, and it is good to see Pakistanis doing it well. A lot of thoughts were going through our minds because we thought Narine would be bowling it. But the guys we sent were the ones who had played well and we thought they would do it for us.

McCullum, losing skipper: It is never nice losing and we are very disappointed in the change room. But it was a thrilling game of T20, only disappointed to come out on the wrong side of it. I thought it was a difficult wicket and as a leader you've got to take some responsibility and take the game deep. You have to credit the opposition, Sami and Russell bowled really well; Misbah lead superbly too. Mustafizur and Sunil Narine were our two options for the super over. It wasn't turning as much as it was in the first innings and Mustafizur is one of the best in the death overs. It was also my fault for not taking that catch in the deep.

Mohammad Sami, MoM: I kept trying to do what we had planned. It was very important to stick to the basics as we didn't have a big target to defend; it was important to win tonight. Really enjoyed this match. [Loose Urdu translation]

00:32 Local Time, 20:32 GMT, 02:02 IST: McCullum stands distraught. Lahore can do everything right for most parts and then everything horribly wrong to mess it up. And how. You would've thought 122 was a cakewalk. You would've thought 15 in the super over is a liberty. Alas. It's never quite to be with Lahore. In the end it comes down to that extra delivery, that wide that Mustafizur bowled. It comes down to Yasir putting down that catch off the final ball of the 20th over. It comes down to McCullum on the final ball of the over when Narine miscued one up in the air. The bottom line will always state that Islamabad are winners tonight. Stay on, the presentations coming your way, Ramiz Raja bringing it to us.

Ball 6: Mustafizur to Russell, SIX, oh Russ. You peach of a beast. Fizz tries to cramp him up with a back of a length, but Russell is quickly onto the back foot, staying up tall and launches into it to deposit it over long-on
Ball 5, Mustafizur to Russell, FOUR, woah. Pulls a bouncer, gets a fat top-edge and it flies away over the keeper. Now then, three off the final ball
Ball 5: Mustafizur to Russell, wide, the horror line. Way too full, way too wide. Losing control of his radar, almost cutting the line of the pitch as it goes through
Ball 4: Mustafizur to Asif, 1 run, tries pulling, under-cutting it off the inside edge to the keeper, who fumbles as well. Russ gets the strike

Ball 3, Mustafizur to Asif, dot, angles it wide on the shorter side. He's flirting with the wide line. Asif tries stretching to reach and stab. Just not enough. And him staring the umpire isn't enough to get him the wide either

Ball 2: Mustafizur to Asif, SIX, oh my. Asif tonks it down, McCullum at the ropes converges with Umar Akmal, neither call, get in each other's way and Baz tries to flick it back. Can't. Over the ropes
Ball 1: Mustafizur to Russell, 1 run, plants the front leg out, goes across the line to the slower cutter and mis-heaves it to mid-wicket in the deep on the bounce
Russell and Asif Ali are out to open. Mustafizur to bowl.

Islamabad need 16. A tie out here would take matters into counting boundaries and Lahore in that case are ahead. Mustafizur is warming up. Narine has one ball and he's running in to shadow practice as well. Now that's a nice way to help mess around with the minds of the United batsmen. Baz leads the huddle ..
Ball 6: Sami to Fakhar, 2 runs, full, outside off and Zaman squeezes out the drive through the covers. Qalandars finish with 15
Ball 5: Sami to Akmal, 1 run, gets it in the blockhole. Akmal falls over as he looks to squeeze it out and toe-ends it down the ground
Ball 4: Sami to Akmal, SIX, another bouncer, Akmal gets some bat on his desperate hook. Top-edges and the pace has enough in it to take it straight bat all the way over the keeper
Ball 3: Sami to Akmal, dot, welcomes him with the nailed in bouncer. Nice height, Akmal tries pulling, hooking, whatever. Can't connect
Umar Akmal walks in
Ball 2: Sami to McCullum, OUT, Tries another one of his pulls, just that this one is shorter and he he miscues it to Samit Patel in the deep behind square

Ball 1: Sami to McCullum, SIX, short, on the waist, going down leg and Baz swivels, pulls and puts his poor timing to bed. It's a new innings and it is a maximum to start off. Over backward square leg
McCullum and Fakhar open the innings. Sami has the ball.

Misbah is out there leading a conference. The washout we had at the start of the day seems ages ago. Right then .. Dean Jones joins his side's huddle in his suit. Forget over-rates, they've never been good, but this discussion is also going on forever. Plenty for the Qalandars to discuss.

My nails are in my tummy. If you thought that yesterday's Sammy heroics were the real deal, today has turned it all around. Lahore never deserved to be in this position at one stage when Salman and Baz out there in the middle. But the break brought the time of luck and things went downhill. Oh the pressures of the tiny target. Forget that .. for now it's an entirely different game. Six balls to smash it everywhere. It's the PSL's first super over. We're told Lahore would be batting first.

Sami to Salman Irshad, out Caught by Asif Ali!! We have a super over. A brute of a delivery on the face, Irshad fends, desperately and square leg takes the balloon. And Islamabad are running in celebrations. How things turn. Salman Irshad c Asif Ali b Sami 6(2) [6s-1]
Sami to Salman Irshad, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Sami to Salman Irshad, SIX, he's equalled it. Moves away, under the cardinal length and slices it high and over extra cover. The Qalandars now can not lose
Mustafizur Rahman, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Sami to Brendon McCullum, out Brendon McCullum Run Out!! Madness. Everyone's tumbling under pressure. McCullum heaves it out to mid-wicket, who dives, recovers and throws it out to Sami, who breaks the stumps. Baz dives, probably never makes it but takes his chance with the ball rolling away to mid-off. And the guy out there throws it to the striker's end. Why? And McCullum has made his way back in. Here we go with the third ump - oh he's killed off the drama. Sami's collection and bail dislodging is as clean as it gets. Brendon McCullum run out (Farhan/Sami) 34(49) [4s-2 6s-1]
Sami to Brendon McCullum, THAT'S OUT!! Run Out!!
Sami to Brendon McCullum, no run, straight on middle off a good length. McCullum tries knocking it back past Sami to run the single. Can't get it past a diving Sami
Mohammad Sami [3.0-0-15-2] is back into the attack
The equation - 7 off 6. It's a debutant at the other end
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, gets the single. Lahore will heave a sigh of relief. With a tickle through mid-wicket
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, no run, long stride. Sees it out with a block
Salman Irshad, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Samit Patel to Yasir Shah, out Caught by Duminy!! Swings, looks to put it into the stands. And guess what, it's only a toe end, without elevation, without distance. Right down long-off's throat. The game turns, ever so slowly. Again. Yasir Shah c Duminy b Samit Patel 3(5)
Samit Patel to Yasir Shah, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!

Samit Patel to Yasir Shah, byes, FOUR, through everyone. Under Shah's agricultural mow, and it goes straight on. Ronchi too looks to collect with the non-existent turn. Oh dear. So very vital. The Qalandars owner is back dancing

Samit Patel to Yasir Shah, 2 runs, heaves it wide of long-on. Russell cleans up quickly, lets out a throw at the non-striker's, deadly accurate and Baz's second was in serious danger. But Patel knocks the bails off with his elbow before he collects
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, happy to take the single with a straight bat down to long-off
Samit Patel [3.0-0-13-2] is back into the attack
Shadab Khan to Yasir Shah, no run, forward, on the defence and sticks his bat out next to his pad to tap it to point
Shadab Khan to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, reads the turn off the back fot, going against it to nudge it in front of square
Shadab Khan to Yasir Shah, 1 run, down the ground with his knock. Sensible
Yasir Shah, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Shadab Khan to Sohail Khan, out Caught by Asif Ali!! Add another. Sohail looked tentative and the lack of intent consumes him. Was the short one from Shadab, that sticks on the surface a little longer. Sohail tries going deep in his crease again to whip it across the line. His heart's just not there. Ends up chipping it up and short mid-wicket dives full-length, left-handed and plucks out a peach. Sohail Khan c Asif Ali b Shadab Khan 0(3)
Shadab Khan to Sohail Khan, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Shadab Khan to Sohail Khan, no run, back foot again. Slapped out to cover. Dot and the required equation is back over six
Shadab Khan to Sohail Khan, no run, stays on the back foot to read the spin in defence
Shadab Khan [3.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
Sohail Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease

A Russell to Narine, out Caught by Misbah!! Can't resist a pull. But the ball has that extra fizz on it, spitting up, surprising Narine with the bounce and gets a fat top edge. Misbah, settles under the skier at cover, deals with the others converging and keeps his calm. Now, now, just when things seem to be going one way .. Narine c Misbah b A Russell 9(4) [4s-2]
A Russell to Narine, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!

A Russell to Narine, FOUR, he's ruining the contest. Where was he hiding? Length, criminal at this stage and Narine takes it through the arc, opening up his stance and cleaning the infield with his muscular slice
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, on the move down, carving it to deep sweeper
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, no run, cutting back in to cramp him up for room. Defends it down the pitch eventually
A Russell to Narine, 1 run, shorter, Narine backs away, pulls and inside-edges it through square leg
A Russell to Narine, FOUR, clears the front leg and treats the yorker with utter disdain. Drilling it away wide of mid-off, who is inside the ring
Sunil Narine, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Faheem Ashraf to Sohail Akhtar, out Caught by Asif Ali!! A steepler. And fine leg does everything to get himself in a real tangle, running all over as he he waits under it, overruns, and then arches back to dive and take it. Oh Lahore are self-combusting, in the way only they can. The pressure gets to Akhtar, he targets the square boundary with his pull. Top-edges eventually. Sohail Akhtar c Sahibzada Farhan b Faheem Ashraf 4(8)
Faheem Ashraf to Sohail Akhtar, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Faheem Ashraf to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, presses forward to steer it square
Faheem Ashraf to Sohail Akhtar, 1 run, to third man
Faheem Ashraf to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, swivels as he pulls it off his tummy to backward square leg
Faheem Ashraf to Brendon McCullum, SIX, gets the release. Finally. It's been a troubled stay, but now decides to walk down for a change, to the pitch of the ball and hoicks it over mid-wicket
Faheem Ashraf to Sohail Akhtar, 1 run, ramps his bat out to run it behind point
Faheem Ashraf, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
A Russell to Sohail Akhtar, 1 run, squeezes it out to third man. Just the two off this over
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, ungainly with his slog. Was never under it, ends up skewing it down to long-on
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, no run, goes shorter. Can't get it away yet again. Another dot played out with this jab to point
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, no run, backs away. But Russell holds his channel outside off. Has to leave it alone in the end
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, no run, tailing in yorker. Jammed out
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, no run, the tight good length without any sort of room. Pushes it out
CRR: 5.93 | REQ: 6.5 -- Things getting tricky
Sami to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, glances it with a hop to fine leg
Sami to Sohail Akhtar, 1 run, taps it to cover off the back foot, Misbah isn't the quickest out there to stop the single
Sami to Sohail Akhtar, no run, in that channel just outside off. A cross-seamer at 146kph and Akhtar flirts, to be beaten by the straightener on the outside edge
Sami to Sohail Akhtar, no run, keeps it tight on the stumps. Another tuck to square leg
Sami to Sohail Akhtar, no run, covers the line with a closed bat face to defend to leg
Sohail Akhtar, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sami to Ramdin, out Caught by Ronchi!! A loud prolonged appeal. And the umpire relents. Is another one of Sami's bouncer and Ramdin stands, looking away, covering his face with his fending hands..pops up off something and Ronchi takes a top one-handed leaper. Now what's that something? Ramdin reckons it's the arm guard. Waits. Reviews. Only to see himself on the giant screen getting a portion of his glove on it as well. Does the game have a twist remaining? Ramdin c Ronchi b Sami 4(7)
Sami to Ramdin, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, no run, flush on the box. Stays low for McCullum's heave's liking and it's that painfully funny blow
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, no run, nails the yorker, tailing in late. Jammed out
A Russell to Ramdin, 1 run, shoulder high bouncer. Ramdin swivels in his pull, gets it to deep square leg
A Russell to Ramdin, no run, pins him on the pad, cutting back in sharply off the turf and beating the inside edge
A Russell to Ramdin, 2 runs, pulls, never mind it coming high off the bat. But safely in the gap wide of short mid-wicket
A Russell to Ramdin, no run, a wristy cut, not quite the timing though as he gets it to point
Andre Russell [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Islamabad would need a few more overs like this one to have a grip on proceedings. A wicket wouldn't harm them either.
Sami to Brendon McCullum, no run, a careful prod in his poke to point
Sami to Brendon McCullum, no run, bang on the money. Denies width, denies length and all McCullum can do is block
Sami to Ramdin, 1 run, width, Ramdin gets across and chops it square
Sami to Ramdin, no run, shuffles, gets behind the line to defend
Denesh Ramdin, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sami to Agha Salman, out Caught by Samit Patel!! There's the break. And then there's the breakthrough. Well directed bouncer at the nose. Salman in his attempt to avoid it goes through with a half-hearted pull. Gets the top-edge and fine leg couldn't have been placed to perfection. Agha Salman c Samit Patel b Sami 48(35) [4s-6 6s-2]
Sami to Agha Salman, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Sami to Brendon McCullum, leg byes, 1 run, into the pads. Sneaks under the bat to grope the thighs and run down to fine leg
Mohammad Sami [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
The equation - 46 needed off 54
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, helps himself to a time-out with a one-kneed drill to long-off
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, no run, clipped, but finds square leg
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, wide, another dart down leg. Misbah ain't amused
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, 3 wides, loses radar. Down leg, spinning further and the keeper can't clean up either. The outfield though doesn't have the pace to take it all the way
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, no run, soft wrists to nudge it through square leg
Duminy to Agha Salman, 1 run, one of the wristy drives to sweeper. Getting low, playing for the angle et al
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, fired wide. Makes McCullum reach out and he does to stab it through the covers
Duminy to Agha Salman, 1 run, on the shorter side. Heaved away to deep mid-wicket
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, 1 run, takes it off the pads and nudges it round the corner
Shadab Khan to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, thick inside-edge as he looks to defend the googly. Runs through square leg
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, 1 run, shortens his length, nudged through mid-wicket
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, SIX, back to crouching down. Another bat swing, another bottom-hander to tonk it into cow corner. He's in a hurry
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, SIX, downtown. Sits, down on a knee and slogs it into the sky. And when it falls it does into long-on. Brutal power
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, no run, loops wide of off. Helps it with the turn towards point
Duminy to Agha Salman, 1 run, 91.8kph, full, dipping into the base of off and is punches straight down the ground
Duminy to Agha Salman, no run, goes reverse. And chips his sweep up on the bounce to backward point
Duminy to Agha Salman, no run, squared up. Outside-edging it eventually to backward point
Duminy to Agha Salman, no run, tries piling on the angle going across to cut. Misses out on the connection
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, on the legs from round the wicket. Tucked through square leg
Duminy to Agha Salman, 1 run, stabs it through to the deep sweeper
Jean-Paul Duminy [1.0-0-6-0] is back into the attack
Shadab Khan to Brendon McCullum, 2 runs, low, to the pitch of it and goes flicking it under his eyeline
Shadab Khan to Brendon McCullum, no run, walks across his stumps, tickles it through his legs to short fine
Shadab Khan to Brendon McCullum, no run, 104.3kph, drifting to leg. Another block follows
Shadab Khan to Brendon McCullum, no run, low forward block
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, 1 run, through the line, for a crunchy drive through the covers
Shadab Khan to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, nice loopy fuller one drawing McCullum forward. And he steers it watchfully, square
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, softly knocks it to long-on, keeps the strike
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, FOUR, wait short. Baz crouches, makes sure he's riding it and flat-bats it behind square. Oh talk about picking gaps
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, no run, 138.3kph, fuller on off. Pushy defence
A Russell to Agha Salman, 1 run, 130.7kph. On a back of a length and Salman uses all of it and the pace to run it to third man
A Russell to Agha Salman, no run, tries a bunt behind point, ends up almost chopping it onto his stumps
A Russell to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, hops up, opens his bat and drops it in front of point to steal a quick one
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, no run, slapped towards cover with the turn
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, FOUR, reads the other one. From middle as it spins in and rolls his wrists to nudge it very fine. So very delicate
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, FOUR, nice inviting flight. Salman goes through the line, hard quick hands and slices it over extra cover
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, no run, on the shorter side again with the googly. Kept out off the back foot
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, no run, a careful poke towards point
Shadab Khan to Agha Salman, no run, starts with a slider. Salman's drive comes off the inside half as it rolls to leg
Shadab Khan, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, no run, waits for the turn to get beside him and dabs it to point with an open bat face
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, no run, all the textbook in his forward block
Samit Patel to Agha Salman, 1 run, quietly knocks it down to long-off
Samit Patel to Agha Salman, FOUR, through cover. So very sloppy. Salman gets a floated half volley and helps himself to a hammering drive .. and the fielder helps him further
Samit Patel to Agha Salman, 2 runs, 93.3kph. He's firing it in. Salman walks across to take matters through mid-wicket. Smart stuff, puts it in the gap too to get back for the second
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, 1 run, backs away, gives himself some room to whack it to a tumbling cover
Sami to Agha Salman, FOUR, make it 12 off this one. Wide, short and cut away with the wrists rolling to get it over the man at slip. And only one way post that
Sami to Agha Salman, no run, rides the bounce, getting up to fend it to leg
Sami to Agha Salman, FOUR, so damn soft. A cross seamer, short as usual and Salman dabs, with some help from the outside edge to run away very fine, beating third man's attempt
Sami to Agha Salman, no run, reaches out, cuts it hard. But point's right there
Sami to Agha Salman, no run, on a back of a length, nipping back in on the tummy. Bunted onto the pitch
Sami to Agha Salman, FOUR, gets the width with the advent of pace. Salman releases the pressure built up with an open-faced punch through sweeper
Mohammad Sami, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, no run, quick feet, but only in the shuffle. No signs of aggression. As yet
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, no run, nice wide tease. McCullum will continue blocking
Samit Patel to Brendon McCullum, no run, tight on off. Can only defend
Samit Patel to Agha Salman, 1 run, deep in the crease to wrist it in front of square
Samit Patel to Agha Salman, no run, half forward, with a swishy drive. Another one beaten on the inside edge
Samit Patel to Agha Salman, no run, in with the arm. Punchy keep-out
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, 2 runs, threads it the gap through the two men around the covers
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, FOUR, smears it through. A long stride to the pitch of the ball and then the freeing of the arms to drill it through the covers
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, no run, forward, a cautiously watching block
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, no run, presses forward to push it to cover
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, no run, opens up his bat face on the front foot to defend it to point
Duminy to Brendon McCullum, no run, shuffles. Back, across, in front of the stumps in defence
Jean-Paul Duminy, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Samit Patel to Agha Salman, no run, full, whipped out off the inside half of the bat. Once again, playing for the turn that's non-existent
Agha Salman, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Samit Patel to Fakhar Zaman, out Lbw!! Lahore are ploding. And this over is never going to end. Too full to be sweeping, Zaman goes with Akmal's flow though, with the spin that's not there. Ends up missing the straighter one and is trapped in front of leg. Now wait, was the ball pitching down leg? It might well have. Why not review again? Fakhar Zaman lbw b Samit Patel 0(1)
Samit Patel to Fakhar Zaman, THAT'S OUT!! Lbw!!
Fakhar Zaman, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Samit Patel to Umar Akmal, out Lbw!! Pay back. Technology denies Patel a review and this time he convinces the umpire to raise his finger. It's Akmal's turn to test the ball tracking. He was always falling over as he tries to flick. The ball goes on with the arm and strikes his front pad. It's an umpire's call .. just kissing leg. Umar Akmal lbw b Samit Patel 4(4) [4s-1]
Samit Patel to Umar Akmal, THAT'S OUT!! Lbw!!

Samit Patel to Umar Akmal, no run, oh drama. Akmal tries another one of his sweeps, and is a sitting duck right in front of his stumps. The United are on appeal .. and then Patel forces Misbah into a review. Here we go, the impact is in line, but it's just spinning past leg
Samit Patel to Umar Akmal, no run, another massive sweep. Just that this one is much slower, gripping on the surface and spinning past
Samit Patel to Umar Akmal, FOUR, oh my. He's happy to come out sweeping. The lines is around off and it's broomed behind square
Umar Akmal and Brendon McCullum are at the crease. Umar Akmal is on strike. Samit Patel will open the attack
Back live. As is the case with the small totals, the powerplay could decide how things go, irrespective of how dodgy this wicket could be. Here we go then ..

Talat gives some respectability to the final total. Islamabad United were down and buried at 70/6, but Talat struck a few meaty blows to take the score past 120. McCullum read the pitch brilliantly and started with spin, Zaman removed Ronchi off the second ball and it was a struggle after that. Yasir and Narine tied down the batsmen and only Duminy seemed to have found a way to score. However, they were still way off target when Talat came out and that's what makes his innings more vital. The ball is turning square and Qalandars will not have an easy time chasing this. Should be fun with the top heavy batting line-up..

Mustafizur to Talat, 2 runs, dropped! Yasir the culprit. He is seen gesturing to Zaman that he lost it under the lights. Short delivery and Talat is not in control of the pull, top-edge skies towards deep square leg and Yasir makes a mess of it
Mohammad Sami, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mustafizur to Shadab Khan, out Caught by Umar Akmal!! One, two, three, four, five and IN. That's how many times Akmal juggled before completing the catch. The off-cutter from Fizz and Shadab picked it early, he was deep in the crease clearing his front leg to have a swing, smashes it straight back over the bowler. Akmal runs across from long-on and does all the circus before taking the catch. Shadab Khan c Umar Akmal b Mustafizur 1(2)
Mustafizur to Shadab Khan, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!

Mustafizur to Talat, 1 run, short and quick, Talat is late on the pull shot, the top-edge thuds into the left shoulder and bobbles away to short third man, just a single. That must have hurt and Talat is seen rubbing it
Mustafizur to Talat, FOUR, bisected deep square leg and deep mid-wicket perfectly. Full toss following a backing away Talat, who flicks it in front of square and collects a much required boundary
Mustafizur to Talat, 2 runs, low full toss and Talat drives it to long-on, placed it wide enough to come back for the second
Mustafizur to Shadab Khan, 1 run, spears in the yorker outside off, Shadab squeezes it to backward point and sprints across. Direct hit would have been curtains for the young leggie
Sohail Khan to Talat, 2 runs, he does. Loopy slower delivery and Talat tries to smash the cover off the ball, dragged off the inside half past square leg and he scampers back for the second
Shadab Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sohail Khan to Faheem Ashraf, out Caught by Narine!! Duck for Ashraf. Full and outside off, Ashraf hammers it flat and straight to long-off. Narine has been in the firing line today and he's hung on to whatever has come his way. Second wicket for Sohail. Can he finish the over well? Faheem Ashraf c Narine b Sohail Khan 0(3)
Sohail Khan to Faheem Ashraf, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Sohail Khan to Faheem Ashraf, wide, down leg and Ashraf swings off his feet, doesn't connect and umpire signals a wide
Sohail Khan to Faheem Ashraf, no run, slower delivery and Ashraf is deceived completely, into the shot early and the ball lobs over the stumps
Sohail Khan to Faheem Ashraf, no run, quick bouncer on the stumps, Ashraf is beaten for pace. The ball flies over the flashing pull shot

Sohail Khan to Talat, 1 run, Akhtar does extremely well to save three. Dug in and Talat pulls it flat towards deep square leg. Akthar was running to take the catch, but slipped and got a hand to make the stop. He was almost left wrongfooted
Faheem Ashraf, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Sohail Khan to Talat, out A Russell Run Out!! Russell is fuming off the ground. Move away people. What was Talat doing? Back of a length outside off, Talat adjusts after making room and punched it to backward point, the single was on and it was Russell's call, Talat does not move after taking a step out, by then Russell is already at the striker's end. Yasir lobs it to Sohail and the rest his history. A Russell run out (Yasir Shah/Sohail Khan) 15(12) [6s-1]
Sohail Khan to Talat, THAT'S OUT!! Run Out!!
Mustafizur to Talat, 1 run, another quick short delivery and this time Talat top-edges the pull in front of deep square leg
Mustafizur to A Russell, 1 run, low full toss outside off, Russell cue-ends down to long-off
Mustafizur to Talat, 1 run, banged in and following Talat, who was backing up, spliced pull to mid-wicket
Mustafizur to A Russell, 1 run, back of a length on the hips, clipped to deep square leg
Mustafizur to Talat, 1 run, fires in the yorker and Talat does well to dig it out to deep backward square leg

Mustafizur to Talat, SIX, Talat is connecting them cleanly. Picked the off-cutter early and waited for it, gave it his everything and managed to clear long-on quite comfortably. Good start to the over
Sohail Khan to A Russell, no run, full and in the slot, Russell went a bit too hard and failed to connect
Sohail Khan to A Russell, wide, now the slower delivery is sprayed outside off, Russell lets go
Sohail Khan to A Russell, wide, banged in and flies over Russell's head, easy call for the umpire
Sohail Khan to Talat, 1 run, off-pace delivery and Talat punches it to point, sets off and makes it past Yasir's throw
Sohail Khan to A Russell, 1 run, slower short of length delivery, Russell delays his cut and hits it towards cover-point, where the fielder goes down in slow-mo and fields the ball

Sohail Khan to A Russell, no run, that would have been an unfortunate way to go. Back of a length ball and Russell flat-bats it straight back at Sohail, who was moving to protect himself, the ball bounces in front of him and hits his boot and lobs to Akmal at mid-off. Ramdin knew it straightaway and he was gesturing to Akmal. But the umpires didn't want to take a chance

Qalandars are appealing for a rebound catch. The umpire asks them to calm down. He has a word with his partner and sends it upstairs. The soft signal is OUT. Fair delivery. Bounced just in front of Sohail. Not Out!
Sohail Khan to Talat, 1 run, runs down and takes it on the full, pushed back to Sohail, who parries it into the off-side

Sohail Khan to Talat, SIX, second one outta here. This time it is Talat. Length delivery on the pads, Talat gives himself some room to free his arms and swings it away over cow corner. New balls, please!
Sohail Khan [2.0-0-8-1] is back into the attack
Mustafizur to Talat, 1 run, on a length and Talat drags the heave off the inner half to deep mid-wicket
Mustafizur to A Russell, 1 run, once more keeps it close to the body, worked away to deep mid-wicket
Mustafizur to A Russell, 2 runs, shortens the length and gives no space, tucked into the vacant mid-wicket region. Easy two
Mustafizur to A Russell, SIX, Dre Russ is in the house peope. Buckle up! Fizz angled it outside off, Russell used his long levers to reach that and clubbed it out of the ground over long-off.
Mustafizur to Talat, 1 run, off-cutter on the pads, clipped to deep backward square leg
Mustafizur to A Russell, 1 run, speared in full and outside off, Russell clears his front leg and mistimes the drive to long-off
Mustafizur Rahman [1.0-0-6-0] is back into the attack

Time-out! Narine and Yasir combined bowling figures - 8-0-30-3. That is eight overs of top class spin bowling. Yes, the surface aided them but they still had to put it in the right areas. Islamabad would be lucky to even reach 110-120 from here.
Narine to Talat, no run, three in a row. At least Islamabad didn't lose a wicket in the over. The flatter offie and Talat is rooted to the crease, hangs his bat out and is lucky not to have edged it
Narine to Talat, no run, now tries a fancy reverse sweep, still does not come off, the ball skids through the surface to beat the swinging blade

Narine to Talat, no run, turn and sharp turn. Talat tries to put him off by moving around the crease, but Narine is too experienced for that, keeps it simple and beats the outside edge with a off-break
Slip and gully now

Narine to A Russell, 1 run, in the air and safe. A mid-wicket would have gobbled that up. The off-break turns in sharply, Russell is early into the nudge to the on-side, the leading edge pops up and drops in no man's land
Narine to A Russell, no run, carrom ball and Russell reads it off the surface, camps in the crease and sees it out
Slip and leg slip waiting
Narine to Talat, 1 run, flighted on leg, Talat kneels and sweeps powerfully to long leg
Sunil Narine [3.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack

Yasir Shah to Talat, 1 run, throws it up outside off, Talat uses his wrists to work it down to long-on. Yasir is done for the night, what amazing figures - 4-0-20-3. His spell has put Qalandars in the ascendancy
Hussain Talat, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Yasir Shah to Duminy, out Lbw!! Duminy is not reviewing this. Tucks his bat and walks off. Does not even have a word with Russell. Second in the over for Yasir and he's got three. The conventional leg-break, pitched outside off and turned in, Duminy plays down the wrong line and is struck in front of off-stump. The ball would have gone on to hit leg. Duminy lbw b Yasir Shah 34(36) [4s-3 6s-1]
Yasir Shah to Duminy, THAT'S OUT!! Lbw!!
Yasir Shah to A Russell, 1 run, fired in on a fullish length, Russell digs it out to long-on
Andre Russell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Short leg to greet Russell

Yasir Shah to Asif Ali, out Bowled!! Timbah! Yasir loved it. Does a Hasan Ali like celebration. A quick cameo from Ali but it needed to be longer. Fraction quicker and Ali is early into the slog sweep, he's through his shot and then the ball arrives to hit middle stump. Asif Ali b Yasir Shah 16(8) [4s-3]
Yasir Shah to Asif Ali, THAT'S OUT!! Bowled!!
Yasir Shah to Asif Ali, FOUR, tossed up outside off, very full in length and Ali had to almost squeeze the drive out square on the off-side, the placement was the key and he got it precise
Yasir Shah to Duminy, 1 run, flighted on leg, worked to deep square leg
Salman Irshad to Asif Ali, no run, dipping full length delivery, at 120kph, Ali squeezes it to cover and looks for a non-existent single, sent back
Salman Irshad to Asif Ali, FOUR, runs starting to flow albeit in a streaky way. Short and outside off, Ali pulls and the inside edge beats Ramdin to his left, Irshad has his hands on his head
Salman Irshad to Asif Ali, 2 runs, pitched up outside off, Ali drills the drive to to deep extra cover, a slip and a fumble allows the duo to steal the second
Salman Irshad to Duminy, 1 run, full and on the legs, clipped past square leg, for a single

Salman Irshad to Asif Ali, 1 run, dropped! Two fielders go for it and one gets a hand. Almost collided into each other. Short and outside off, Ali wanted to hit it straight back, but skies it off the cue-end towards sweeper cover. Baz was running back from cover and he got a hand to it. Should have left it to the sweeper

Salman Irshad to Asif Ali, FOUR, six followed by a four, high time for Islamabad to get a move on. Irshad drifted on the legs and Ali used the pace on the ball to flick it through backward square leg, raced away
Salman Irshad [1.0-0-7-1] is back into the attack

Yasir Shah to Duminy, SIX, fabulous shot! Yasir is not happy with himself and rightly so. He gave width for Duminy to free his arms, the South African bent his back knee and lofted it inside out over extra cover. All the way!
Yasir Shah to Duminy, no run, tossed up on off, Duminy defends it back to Yasir
Yasir Shah to Asif Ali, 1 run, blocked off the outer edge to backward point, quick single
Yasir Shah to Duminy, 1 run, floated up outside off, Duminy mistimes the drive to long-off
Asif Ali, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Yasir Shah to Samit Patel, out Caught by Narine!! That looked to be clearing long-on, but Narine took it well inside the rope. Patel fetches the googly from outside off and goes for the slog sweep, seemed to have struck it sweetly but the drag might have caused a cue-end. Narine didn't move an inch to take that. Samit Patel c Narine b Yasir Shah 9(10) [4s-1]
Yasir Shah to Samit Patel, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Yasir Shah to Samit Patel, no run, low dipping full toss and Patel jams it back to Yasir
Narine to Duminy, no run, fraction quicker and Duminy defends within himself, another testing over from Narine
Gully added

Narine to Duminy, 2 runs, spin and Duminy plays it well this time. Waits for the ball to turn and then has a poke at that with soft hands, the outside edge runs past Baz at slip and the duo scamper back
Narine to Samit Patel, 1 run, shortens the length on the carrom ball, held up on the wicket as well, Patel chops it into the off-side
Narine to Samit Patel, no run, carrom ball and Patel reacts late, steers it to backward point with an angled bat
Narine to Duminy, 1 run, flighted on off, Duminy plays an extended forward block past cover

Narine to Duminy, no run, beauty! Duminy has a look at the surface. He is beaten comprehensively. Another Narine offie that pitches outside leg and turns away, beating the outside edge and striking the back pad
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-4-0] is back into the attack
Yasir Shah to Duminy, 1 run, flatter in trajectory and Duminy nudges it through mid-wicket
Yasir Shah to Samit Patel, 1 run, drifting into the pads, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Yasir Shah to Duminy, 1 run, advances and almost yorks himself, squeezed past a diving Yasir and to long-on
Yasir Shah to Duminy, no run, flighted and turning in, Duminy presses forward and blocks
Yasir Shah to Duminy, no run, quicker and close to off, Duminy goes right back and defends
Yasir Shah to Samit Patel, 1 run, very full and it is an easy knock for Patel down to long-on
Salman Irshad to Samit Patel, 1 run, fuller and curling in, Patel wrists the drive to long-on
Salman Irshad to Duminy, 1 run, back of a length around off, Duminy bunts it into the off-side - between cover-point and cover
Salman Irshad to Samit Patel, 1 run, short and outside off, Patel slaps the cut to sweeper cover
Salman Irshad to Samit Patel, no run, good length ball on off, Patel knocks it back down the wicket
Salman Irshad to Samit Patel, FOUR, slingy back of a length delivery around the ribs, Patel is not too perturbed by the pace, gets inside the line and tickles it to the fine leg fence, off the mark
Samit Patel, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Salman Irshad to Misbah, out Caught by Ramdin!! What a debut! First game in PSL and Salman Irshad has got the big fish. He was marked as bowler to watch out for at the toss and he delivers rightaway. A round-armish action and at a sharp pace, the length was short and Misbah was trying to steer it to third man, climbs awkwardly to take the outside edge and flew to Ramdin, who somehow managed to cling on. The young man is elated and jumping up in joy. Misbah c Ramdin b Salman Irshad 4(10)
Salman Irshad to Misbah, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Salman Irshad, comes into the attack
Yasir Shah to Duminy, no run, flighted around off, Duminy pushes and the thickish inside edge rolls into the on-side, Yasir tidies up

Yasir Shah to Duminy, no run, excellent review. The first instance that looked plumb. But Duminy and Misbah got it spot on. The wrong 'un on a shortish length, Duminy went deep in the crease to play the pull and missed it because of the turn, struck on the back thigh. The ball pitched outside leg and the rest does not matter. Baz has a word with the umpire to know what exactly was the issue and Misbah comes around to have a chat

Review: Duminy is given out LBW. He has a word with Misbah and decides to challenge the decision. Fair delivery. This looks dead. No inside edge as confirmed by the UltraEdge. Ball tracking shows it to be pitching outside leg. Not Out!

Yasir Shah to Duminy, no run, how did that miss off? Looped up leg-break outside off, Duminy saw the length and went for the drive, didn't account for the spin and is beaten on the inside edge. Yasir had his hands on his head
Yasir Shah to Misbah, 1 run, dragged back length and Misbah pulls it to deep mid-wicket, just a single
Yasir Shah to Misbah, no run, charges down and Yasir shortens the length, Misbah adjusts to the turn and cuts it to backward point
Slip in place
Yasir Shah to Misbah, no run, quicker and around off, Misbah chops the cut to backward point
Yasir Shah, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Narine to Duminy, no run, flighted on leg and middle, Duminy blocks it to backward point
Narine to Misbah, 1 run, shortens the length and that allows Misbah to play the punch square of the wicket, single to sweeper
Narine to Duminy, 1 run, tossed up and Duminy plays a compact forward defence, right in between point and cover
Narine to Misbah, 1 run, carrom ball and Misbah reads it off the surface, eases it past cover

Narine to Misbah, no run, throws it up teasingly and Misbah takes the bait - down on one knee to play the sweep, tried to fetch it from outside off and missed it altogether, turned in and beat the inside edge
Narine to Misbah, no run, flatter and on the stumps, Misbah knocks it back down
Mustafizur to Duminy, no run, retorts to the fast offie and Duminy chops the cut in front of backward point
Mustafizur to Duminy, FOUR, that is not the place to bowl on this surface - short and wide outside off, Duminy is right on top of that, cutting it past the diving backward point fielder
Mustafizur to Duminy, no run, fuller and just outside off, Duminy blocks with an angled bat to point
Mustafizur to Misbah, 1 run, another fast off-cutter from the Fizz, Misbah dabs it right between gully and backward point, single to third man
Mustafizur to Misbah, no run, off-cutter on a length, Misbah presses forward and pushes to cover
Mustafizur to Duminy, 1 run, back of a length around off, Duminy punches with an open bat face to third man
Mustafizur Rahman, comes into the attack
Narine to Duminy, 1 run, carrom ball and Duminy certainly didn't read it, played for the off-break and it squirted off the inside edge to square leg. Misbah calls him through for a quick single
Narine to Duminy, no run, shortens the length and Duminy turns it to short mid-wicket, not in conrtol
Narine to Duminy, no run, this is unplayable. Flighted on off, Duminy is drawn into the forward push, lunges forward but is beaten on the outside edge by the sharp turn
Narine to Duminy, no run, quicker and at the stumps, Duminy bunts it into the off-side
Narine to Duminy, no run, tossed up on leg-stump, Duminy watchfully defends back
Slip in now
Narine to Duminy, no run, ripper! Pitched outside leg and ended up outside off. Not much Duminy could have done about that. He pressed forward to defend but was beaten neck and crop
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Misbah-ul-Haq, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, out Caught by Narine!! Third time unlucky for Farhan. He kept attempting the pull shot, didn't connect twice off Sohail and this time he picks out long-on. The delivery climbs more than he expected and hit the higher part of the bat, straight down Narine's throat. Sahibzada Farhan c Narine b Sohail Khan 6(16)
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, THAT'S OUT!! Caught!!
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, straighter bat and punches towards cover, where the fielder swoops down quickly
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, once more Farhan selects the wrong length to play the pull, back of a length and he splices it along the ground straight to mid-off
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, back of a length on off, knocked back to Sohail
Sohail Khan to Duminy, 1 run, on a length close to off, Duminy drives and the inside edge thuds into the pad, rolls in front of cover and the pair take off, easily done
Sohail Khan to Duminy, FOUR, wrong line. Down leg and Duminy clips it neatly through backward square. Raced across the turf. No signs of a slow outfield due to rain
Fakhar Zaman to Duminy, 1 run, floated up outside off, Duminy shimmies down and wrists it to long-on
Fakhar Zaman to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run, rushes on from back of a length and Farhan is late on the pull, mistimed through mid-wicket
Fakhar Zaman to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, slower and around off, Farhan checks his push and plays it back to Zaman
Fakhar Zaman to Duminy, 1 run, nurdled with the spin to deep mid-wicket

Fakhar Zaman to Duminy, FOUR, overcooks the flighted delivery and lands it full, Duminy drills it down the ground past his partner. There was a fielder at long-on but he could only watch it crash into the cushions
Fakhar Zaman to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run, fraction short and Farhan slaps it to wide long-off
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run, bit of space outside off and Farhan throws the bat at it, thickish outside edge to third man
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, drifting on the pads, Farhan misses the glance and the ball rolls off the pad to Ramdin

Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, 2 runs, dropped? No. Short of length outside off, Farhan flat-bats it to the left of Sohail, who does not bend down in time. Well past his fingers and Baz from mid-off tidies up
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, an encore of the last delivery, Farhan taps it to short mid-wicket
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, back of a length and tucked gently to short mid-wicket
Sohail Khan to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, fuller and around off, Farhan is reluctant to come forward as he pushes from the crease to cover
Sohail Khan, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Fakhar Zaman to Sahibzada Farhan, 1 run, drifting in and Farhan nudges it off the inner half of the bat to mid-wicket
Fakhar Zaman to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, slower and hint of turn, Farhan is through the cut shot and the ball arrived later
Fakhar Zaman to Sahibzada Farhan, no run, skids on and Farhan is tentative in his forward prod, ekes out an inside edge onto the pad
Fakhar Zaman to Duminy, 1 run, on the back foot for a punch down the ground
Jean-Paul Duminy, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Fakhar Zaman to Ronchi, out Bowled!! Through the slog. Oh my. Ronchi does it horribly wrong. Gets his leg away, exposes his stumps and tries dispatching it away. The ball though sneaks and takes the leg-bail. Ronchi b Fakhar Zaman 0(2)
Fakhar Zaman to Ronchi, THAT'S OUT!! Bowled!!
Fakhar Zaman to Ronchi, no run, holds it back, slowly coming in with the angle. Ronchi waits, checking his defence
Ronchi and Sahibzada Farhan are at the crease. Ronchi is on strike. Fakhar Zaman will open the attack
Off we go then. Some loopy left-armers to get us going.

Rumman Raees, who jarred his knee during the last game and was stretchered out, is not playing today. Foreign players - Chadwick Walton and Steven Finn miss out. Dre Russ is back and so is Samit Patel. For Qalandars, young pace sensation Shaheen Afridi makes way for another raw and young fast bowler - Salman Irshad.
Teams:
Lahore Qalandars (Playing XI): Brendon McCullum(c), Sunil Narine, Fakhar Zaman, Umar Akmal, Denesh Ramdin(w), Agha Salman, Sohail Akhtar, Yasir Shah, Mustafizur Rahman, Sohail Khan, Salman Irshad
Islamabad United (Playing XI): Luke Ronchi(w), Sahibzada Farhan, Jean-Paul Duminy, Samit Patel, Misbah-ul-Haq(c), Hussain Talat, Andre Russell, Asif Ali, Shadab Khan, Faheem Ashraf, Mohammad Sami

Misbah: We need to bat better. Whether we are batting first or batting second we need to look to score big. We could have done better with the bowling as well, understanding the conditions and bowling better lengths into the pitch. It is a packed house, a Friday and hopefully we will give them a good show.

Baz: We are going to have a bowl first. A little bit of rain and the wicket has been under cover all through so we don't know how it is going to behave. We know we have to smoothen up a few rough edges and that's what we'll focus on. The pitch does look a bit tacky, it is a good wicket and a great place to bat.
Lahore Qalandars have won the toss and have opted to field
Pakistan Super League's twitter handle helps us with this - "Toss delayed by half an hour. Play will start at 8:30 pm subject to no further rain." Fingers crossed.

Match #12: After the damp squib that the afternoon game was, we are back, with more of hope. The news out there is that the rain has stopped, but the outfield has taken a beating. Never mind how many overs they manage to squeeze in, nobody needs these two points more than the teams languishing at the bottom, and that's what makes this clash all the more special. Lahore with the hope to course correct, not just for this season but correct a wretched history in the PSL. Islamabad on the other hand would be hoping to not lose momentum like they did the other night. Wait in, hopefully something good thrown our way ..
Teams:

Islamabad United (From): Luke Ronchi(w), Chadwick Walton, Asif Ali, Jean-Paul Duminy, Misbah-ul-Haq(c), Hussain Talat, Faheem Ashraf, Shadab Khan, Rumman Raees, Mohammad Sami, Steven Finn, Amad Butt, Alex Hales, Sam Billings, Mohammad Hasan, Samit Patel, Andre Russell, Samuel Badree, Rohail Nazir, Zafar Gohar, Iftikhar Ahmed, Sahibzada Farhan

Lahore Qalandars (From): Brendon McCullum(c), Sunil Narine, Fakhar Zaman, Umar Akmal, Denesh Ramdin(w), Sohail Akhtar, Agha Salman, Sohail Khan, Shaheen Afridi, Anton Devcich, Aamer Yamin, Bilal Asif, Cameron Delport, Ghulam Mudassar, Bilawal Bhatti, Mitchell McClenaghan, Kyle Abbott, Raza Hasan, Yasir Shah, Gulraiz Sadaf

latest_video.comm: Sami to Salman Irshad, out Caught by Asif Ali!! We have a super over. A brute of a delivery on the face, Irshad fends, desperately and square leg takes the balloon. And Islamabad are running in celebrations. How things turn. Salman Irshad c Asif Ali b Sami 6(2) [6s-1]
